{"title":"Samter NERD","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/Samter NERD iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Tríada de Samter\\N(N-ERD)","guid":"QcpPgtCwxg_KZcb9VTOI8w","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Nomenclatura\\Ny Definición","guid":"92FEqBkx499UTqi3WO7fwQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Tríada de Samter → epónimo histórico (Max Samter, 1967)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Nombres\\Nactuales","guid":"QVhSIdJc2_h8YBwSgNToSQ","children":[{"id":"4","parent":"3","text":"N-ERD → NSAID-Exacerbated Respiratory Disease (preferido)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"3","text":"AERD → Aspirin-Exacerbated Respiratory Disease","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"3","text":"Enfermedad de Widal (nomenclatura europea clásica)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Tríada\\Nclásica","guid":"QuD9tG58f-UiArsZlqQ0oQ","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"1. Asma bronquial (moderada-grave)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"2. Rinosinusitis crónica con poliposis nasal (CRSwNP)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"7","text":"3. Intolerancia a AINEs/aspirina → inhibidores COX-1","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"1","text":"Afecta ~1.4 millones de personas en EE.UU.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"1","text":"NO es alergia mediada por IgE → mecanismo farmacológico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"Prevalencia general: ~0.5-1% de la población adulta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"En asmáticos: 10-20% (subestimada por falta de provocación)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"En CRSwNP: hasta 30-40%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"13","text":"Inicio típico: 3ª-4ª década de vida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"13","text":"Predominio femenino (2:1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"13","text":"Historia familiar\\Npositiva: 67% de casos\\N(estudio finlandés)","guid":"pzNKohLTbjIcRPp6CkXgtQ","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"Primer grado familiar con asma: 55%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"Poliposis nasal en familiar: 21%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"19","text":"Intolerancia a AINEs en familiar: 20%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"19","text":"N-ERD en familiar directo: 11%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"13","text":"→ SUSCEPTIBILIDAD GENÉTICA demostrada (no puramente adquirida)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"0","text":"Fisiopatología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"Eje central: METABOLISMO DEL ÁCIDO ARAQUIDÓNICO","guid":"eOOEL_VwUt26icgQ60CbQw","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"Mecanismo\\Nprincipal","guid":"SDlgNTwT07nnzEtiWKC-OA","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"Inhibición COX-1 → ↓ PGE2 (antiinflamatoria)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"PGE2 normalmente frena mastocitos y eosinófilos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"27","text":"Desvío hacia vía 5-LOX → ↑↑ leucotrienos cisteinílicos (CysLTs)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"LTC4, LTD4, LTE4 → broncoespasmo + edema mucoso","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"27","text":"↓ PGE2 + ↑ CysLTs → tormenta inflamatoria aguda","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"25","text":"Células\\Nclave","guid":"tP61_oM5mYJ41AeYYr9MZw","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"MASTOCITOS → fuente principal\\Nde CysLTs y PGD2","guid":"nAMrfOFGjDtmqPEKZhu89w","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Activados directamente por inhibición COX-1","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"Diana terapéutica prioritaria","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"33","text":"EOSINÓFILOS → inflamación\\Ncrónica tipo 2 (T2)","guid":"I3BSksLvxENS7tvKb0Aiyg","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"↑ IL-5, IL-4, IL-13","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"Infiltran mucosa nasal y bronquial","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"40","parent":"33","text":"PLAQUETAS →\\Npapel emergente","guid":"u4xKZ_JeKdOy-EnV2fQY5g","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"Fuente adicional de CysLTs","guid":"tgcv_U0UOufBsCjWEF1nOA","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"40","text":"Potencian respuesta inflamatoria aguda","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"25","text":"Mediadores\\Nclave","guid":"Pmqgd0rLb6jQ9NBASYLiyA","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"PGD2 ↑↑ → vasodilatación, broncoconstricción","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"43","text":"CysLTs ↑↑ → síntoma cardinal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"43","text":"Eotaxina, periostin → remodelado de mucosa","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"25","text":"Inflamación\\Ncrónica tipo 2\\N(T2)","guid":"-8_ncN1h2UKwpb67_rRTyA","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"IL-4, IL-13 → producción IgE + remodelado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"IL-5 → eosinofilia periférica y tisular","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"47","text":"Periostin → marcador de actividad eosinofílica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"25","text":"Cambios en lipidoma y\\Ntransmetabolismo celular","guid":"kKjv8AIO3yg5AdEEtuwy9Q","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"Disregulación crónica de metabolismo lipídico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"Contribución de microbioma nasal (investigación activa)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"0","text":"Presentación\\NClínica","guid":"lhAAKku_FxWGnumJQG16yg","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"Componente\\Nnasosinusal","guid":"C7GFAmkUz4DuowvdyYbYqg","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"CRSwNP severa y RECURRENTE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Poliposis etmoidal bilateral característica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Alta tasa de recurrencia post-cirugía sin tratamiento","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"59","parent":"55","text":"Anosmia (frecuente, impacto en calidad de vida)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"55","text":"Obstrucción nasal crónica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"55","text":"Rinorrea mucopurulenta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"55","text":"Síntomas de rinosinusitis recurrente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"63","parent":"54","text":"Componente\\Nbronquial","guid":"GZImF-X31Q9HucTVFrggpg","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"Asma MODERADA-GRAVE","guid":"","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"FEV1 disminuido en muchos pacientes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"Mal control a pesar de tratamiento estándar","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"63","text":"Broncoespasmo recurrente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"63","text":"Crisis asmáticas frecuentes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"54","text":"Reacción aguda a AINEs (típica)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"Aparece 30-120 minutos post-ingesta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"Síntomas nasales: rinorrea profusa, obstrucción intensa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"69","text":"Síntomas bronquiales: sibilancias, disnea, tos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"69","text":"Síntomas extrarrespiratorios (10-30%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Urticaria, angioedema","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"Enrojecimiento facial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"76","parent":"73","text":"Irritación ocular (conjuntivitis)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"73","text":"Náuseas, malestar gastrointestinal","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"78","parent":"54","text":"Síntomas extrarrespiratorios raros","guid":"","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"Hipotensión (reacción sistémica severa)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"54","text":"Patrón de progresión típico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"1° → rinitis perenne → 2° → poliposis nasal → 3° → asma → 4° → intolerancia AINEs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"Años de intervalo entre componentes","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"DIAGNÓSTICO CLÍNICO en la mayoría de los casos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"83","text":"Criterios diagnósticos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"Tríada completa = DIAGNÓSTICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"Tríada incompleta + historia sugestiva → provocación","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"88","parent":"83","text":"Gold standard diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"89","parent":"88","text":"PRUEBA DE PROVOCACIÓN CON ASPIRINA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Vía oral (protocolo AAO/AAAAI) → más frecuente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"Vía intranasal (lisina-aspirina) → más segura, menos sensible","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"Vía bronquial (inhalada) → uso restringido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"89","text":"Requiere consentimiento + monitorización estricta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"89","text":"Contraindicada si FEV1 <70% del predicho","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"83","text":"Biomarkers diagnósticos y de seguimiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"Eosinófilos en sangre periférica ↑","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"FeNO (óxido nítrico exhalado) ↑","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"95","text":"IgE total elevada (frecuente)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"95","text":"LTE4 urinario ↑↑ (investigación / no disponible rutina)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"95","text":"Periostin sérico ↑","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"83","text":"Diagnóstico diferencial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"Asma alérgica + poliposis independiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"Intolerancia a AINEs no asmática","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"101","text":"Síndrome NSAID-induced urticaria/angioedema (distinto mecanismo)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"105","parent":"101","text":"Mastocitosis sistémica","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"106","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"Evitación de AINEs/aspirina → PILAR FUNDAMENTAL","guid":"","children":[{"id":"108","parent":"107","text":"Inhibidores COX-2 selectivos (celecoxib): TOLERADOS generalmente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"107","text":"Paracetamol: tolerado a dosis bajas (<1g), precaución a dosis altas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"107","text":"EVITAR: ibuprofeno, naproxeno, diclofenaco, ketorolaco, AAS","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"106","text":"Tratamiento del asma","guid":"","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Corticoides inhalados + LABA (base)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Montelukast (antagonista CysLT receptor) → especialmente útil en N-ERD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"111","text":"Zileutón (inhibidor 5-LOX) → no disponible en Chile","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"106","text":"Tratamiento de CRSwNP","guid":"","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Corticoides intranasales (fluticasona, mometasona)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"Lavados nasales con solución salina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"Corticoides sistémicos en brotes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"106","text":"Cirugía endoscópica sinusal (FESS)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"Indicada en poliposis refractaria","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"Mejora síntomas y acceso tópico de corticoides","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"ALTA TASA DE RECURRENCIA sin tratamiento adyuvante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"119","text":"Resultados comparables entre grupos etarios","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"106","text":"Desensibilización a aspirina (ATAD)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"INDICACIÓN SELECCIONADA post-FESS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"Mecanismo: tolerancia farmacológica progresiva","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"Protocolo: inicio dosis muy bajas (20-40mg) → escalada hasta 325-650mg/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"124","text":"Mantenimiento: aspirina 325-650mg c/12h de por vida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"129","parent":"124","text":"Eficacia clínica post-desensibilización","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"↓ recurrencia de pólipos nasales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"↓ exacerbaciones asmáticas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"↓ necesidad de cirugía de revisión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"129","text":"↑ sentido del olfato","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"124","text":"Contraindicaciones: úlcera péptica activa, anticoagulación, FEV1 <70%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"124","text":"Requiere infraestructura hospitalaria (servicio de alergia + ORL)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"106","text":"Terapia biológica → CAMBIO DE PARADIGMA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"DUPILUMAB (anti-IL-4Rα → bloquea IL-4/IL-13)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"Aprobado FDA para AERD con CRSwNP + asma","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"↑ tolerancia a AASa 40% (RCT Sánchez et al. 2023)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"137","text":"Efecto sobre anosmia: significativo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"137","text":"Primera línea biológica en N-ERD severo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"142","parent":"136","text":"OMALIZUMAB (anti-IgE)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"143","parent":"142","text":"↑ tolerancia AAS 60% (estudio Sánchez et al. 2023)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"142","text":"Mejora FEV1, FVC, control asmático (Cameli et al. 2019)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"142","text":"Restauración de tolerancia a aspirina documentada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"142","text":"Útil en N-ERD con atopia + IgE elevada","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"136","text":"MEPOLIZUMAB (anti-IL-5)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"Reduce eosinófilos periféricos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"Tolerancia AAS ~22% (Sánchez et al. 2023) → menor efecto","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"150","parent":"136","text":"BENRALIZUMAB (anti-IL-5Rα)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"151","parent":"150","text":"Tolerancia AAS ~22% → similar a mepolizumab","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"136","text":"COMPARACIÓN: omalizumab > dupilumab > mepolizumab ~ benralizumab (para tolerancia AAS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"136","text":"ELECCIÓN BIOLÓGICO: basada en fenotipo (IgE, eosinófilos, atopia)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones ORL Geriátricas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"155","parent":"154","text":"Presentación en adulto mayor","guid":"","children":[{"id":"156","parent":"155","text":"Poliposis nasal más prevalente con la edad → solapamiento con N-ERD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"155","text":"Anosmia → diagnóstico diferencial con presbyosmia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"155","text":"Riesgo de reacción adversa a AINEs subestimado (polifarmacia)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"159","parent":"154","text":"Polifarmacia y N-ERD","guid":"","children":[{"id":"160","parent":"159","text":"AINEs frecuentes en adulto mayor (analgesia, antiinflamatorio)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"159","text":"AINES → precipitante de crisis asmáticas graves","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"159","text":"AAS en dosis antiagregante (100mg) → PUEDE desencadenar reacción","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"159","text":"Revisar siempre indicación de AAS en paciente con asma + poliposis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"159","text":"Alternativas analgésicas: paracetamol, opioides bajos, tramadol","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"165","parent":"154","text":"Cirugía ORL en adulto mayor frágil","guid":"","children":[{"id":"166","parent":"165","text":"FESS: factible y segura en seleccionados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"165","text":"Evaluar comorbilidades, función pulmonar, estado funcional (CFS)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"165","text":"Procedimientos en consulta como alternativa en frágiles","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"169","parent":"154","text":"Biológicos en adulto mayor","guid":"","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"Escasa representación en ensayos clínicos (>70 años)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"169","text":"Datos de seguridad aceptables en poblaciones de mediana edad","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"169","text":"Considerar costo, adherencia, comorbilidades inmunomoduladoras","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 1: Asma de control difícil + CRSwNP recurrente = DESCARTAR N-ERD SIEMPRE","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 2: Preguntar activamente por intolerancia a ibuprofeno/naproxeno — muchos pacientes no lo reportan espontáneamente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 3: AAS 100mg como antiagregante puede desencadenar reacción → revisar en todo asmático con poliposis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 4: Celecoxib e inhibidores COX-2 son SEGUROS en N-ERD confirmado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 5: Paracetamol a dosis bajas (<1g) es tolerado en la mayoría; precaución a dosis >1g","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 6: Montelukast es fármaco de elección complementario en N-ERD (actúa en vía CysLT)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 7: Post-FESS + aspirina desensitización = mejor estrategia combinada para ↓ recurrencia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 8: Dupilumab tiene aprobación regulatoria para CRSwNP + asma en N-ERD → considerar antes de reoperar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 9: En adulto mayor, la anosmia por N-ERD puede confundirse con presbyosmia — el contexto clínico (asma, poliposis) orienta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"173","text":"PERLA 10: NO existe N-ERD con COX-2 selectivos → estos son seguros para analgesia en el adulto mayor con esta condición","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"→ Módulo 3 — Nariz y Olfato (ORL Geriátrica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"184","text":"→ Módulo 7 — Integración ORL en VGI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"184","text":"→ Presbifagia (polifarmacia y mucosa)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"188","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"189","parent":"188","text":"1. Ley-Tomas JJ et al. N-ERD: molecular mechanism, management and treatment. Front Allergy. 2024;5:1462985. DOI: 10.3389/falgy.2024.1462985","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"188","text":"2. Lyly A, Laidlaw TM, Lundberg M. Pathomechanisms of AERD-Recent Advances. Front Allergy. 2021;2:734733. DOI: 10.3389/falgy.2021.734733","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"188","text":"3. Stevens WW et al. The role of aspirin desensitization... J Allergy Clin Immunol. 2021;147(3):827-844. DOI: 10.1016/j.jaci.2020.10.043","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"188","text":"4. Walters BK et al. AERD and the Unified Airway: A Contemporary Review. Otolaryngol Clin North Am. 2023;56(1):107-124. DOI: 10.1016/j.otc.2022.09.008","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"188","text":"5. Sánchez J et al. NSAID Tolerance After Biological Therapy in N-ERD: RCT. J Allergy Clin Immunol Pract. 2023;11(7):2172-2179. DOI: 10.1016/j.jaip.2023.04.033","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"188","text":"6. Cameli P et al. Omalizumab treatment in Samter triad: case series and review. Eur Rev Med Pharmacol Sci. 2019;23(18):8124-8129. DOI: 10.26355/eurrev_201909_19031","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"188","text":"7. Laidlaw TM. Pathogenesis of NSAID-induced reactions in AERD. World J Otorhinolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2018;4(3):162-168. DOI: 10.1016/j.wjorl.2018.08.001","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"188","text":"8. Suikkila A et al. Inheritance of NSAID-Exacerbated Respiratory Disease. Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2023;168(3):540-543. DOI: 10.1177/01945998221102085","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":196,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"Samter NERD iPad","id":"map_855","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Samter NERD iPad"}